            <person xml:id="pers1461">
               <p>Born in <placeName>London</placeName> to <persName>Thomas Wilkins
                     Morgan</persName> Esq. and his wife <persName>Elizabeth (nee
                  Russell</persName>), Elizabeth Mary&apos;s parents sent her to live in
                     <placeName>Bristol</placeName> during her teens, where she had some connection
                  with <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2221.xml"/>Whitefield</persName>&apos;s
                  Tabernacle in Kingswood. After she came of age Elizabeth was again in
                     <placeName>Bristol</placeName>, lodging with <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers0373.xml"/>Anne Chapman</persName>, where she became
                  friends with <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2192.xml"/>Sarah Wesley
                     Jr</persName>. and her family, as well as a correspondent of <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>. In <date when="1787"
                     >1787</date> Morgan married <persName>Ely Bates</persName> (d. <date
                     when="1812">1812</date>). Prior to her marriage Morgan had aligned with the
                  Moravians, and after her husband&apos;s death she withdrew from society into their
                  community in <placeName>Okbrook, Derbyshire</placeName> (and latter to
                     <placeName>Gracehill</placeName>, <placeName>Antrim</placeName>,
                     <placeName>Ireland</placeName>). See Mrs. T. G. Tyndale, <hi rend="italic"
                     >Selections from the correspondence of Mrs. Ely Bates, and incidents of her
                     early life </hi>(<placeName>Oxford</placeName>, <date from="1872" to="1873"
                     >1872–73</date>).</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
